}}\n* Portuguese: {{t+|pt|passarinho|m}} {{qualifier|Brazil, childish}}\n}}\n{{trans-bottom}}\n\n=====See also=====\n* {{l|en|birb}}\n* {{l|en|burd}}\n* {{l|en|chirp}}\n* {{l|en|ornithic}}\n* {{l|en|ornithology}}\n* {{l|en|squawk}}\n* {{l|en|tweet}}\n* [[Appendix: Animals]]\n* [[Appendix:Gestures/middle finger]]\n\n====Verb====\n{{en-verb}}\n\n# {{lb|en|intransitive}} To observe or identify [[wild]] birds in their [[natural]] [[environment]].\n# {{lb|en|intransitive}} To catch or shoot birds; to hunt birds.\n# {{lb|en|intransitive|figuratively}} To seek for game or plunder; to [[thieve]].\n#* {{RQ:Jonson Alchemist\n|passage=MAMMON: These day-owls.<br>SURLY: That are '''birding''' in men's purses}}\n# {{lb|en|transitive|television}} To [[transmit]] via [[satellite]].\n#* {{quote-text|en|year=1995|author=David D. Pearce|title=Wary Partners: Diplomats and the Media|page=43\n|passage=Unless the TV crew has its own flyaway, the locals can still defeat a story they couldn't prevent reporters from covering by cutting it off at the pass, when it is being '''birded''' through their facilities.}}\n#* {{quote-text|en|year=2012|author=Yoel Cohen|title=Media Diplomacy|page=127\n|passage=After being sent by fast car to Tel Aviv the cassettes would be ''''birded'''<nowiki/>' by satellite to the USA and London.}}\n\n=====Translations=====\n{{trans-top|to hunt birds}}\n* Unami: {{t|unm|nuchchulënse}}\n{{trans-bottom}}\n\n====Adjective====\n{{en-adj|birdier<l:rare>}}\n\n# {{lb|en|Canada|colloquial|of a school or university course}} Able to be [[pass]]ed with very little work; having the nature of a [[bird course]].\n#* {{quote-web|en|date=Oct 16 2020|author=illegalsalt|title=Thoughts on these bird courses|site=Reddit|location=r/UTM|url=https://www.reddit.com/r/UTM/comments/jccoym/thoughts_on_these_bird_courses/g90m3as/|text=SOC100 isn’t '''bird''' at all lol. But ANT101 is super easy & the prof (Dr. Sherry Fukuzawa) is amazing.}}\n#* {{quote-web|en|date=Jun 17 2022|author=ConradIsMyDaddy|title=How to Graduate from the University of Waterloo's Computer Science Program with the Least Amount of Effort|site=Reddit|location=r/uwaterloo|url=https://www.reddit.com/r/uwaterloo/comments/vejv35/how_to_graduate_from_the_university_of_waterloos/|text=but admittedly, all the hours spent creating excel sheets optimizing my course plan, all the research finding the absolutely best professors, all the smart friends i made, all the alumni i contacted to collect crowdmarks of past exams, all the research i did finding the '''birdiest''' courses of all...... all of it was wayyyyyy more fun to me than just sitting down and studying like a normal kid. it was kind of just like playing a video game.}}\n\n===Etymology 2===\nOriginally Cockney rhyming slang, shortened from ''[[bird-lime]]'' for \"[[time]]\".\n\n====Noun====\n{{en-noun|-}}\n\n# {{lb|en|slang}} A [[prison]] [[sentence]].\n#: {{ux|en|He’s doing '''bird'''.}}\n#* {{quote-book|en|year=2012|author=Theodore Dalrymple|title=If Symptoms Persist|text=Well, I’ll do my '''bird''' - I can ‘andle it, '''bird’s''' never been no trouble for me - and then I’ll get you.}}\n\n=====Synonyms=====\n* {{sense|prison sentence}} {{l|en|porridge}}, {{l|en|stretch}}, {{l|en|time}}\n\n=====Translations=====\n{{trans-top|prison sentence}}\n{{trans-bottom}}\n<!-- some translations from the box below may belong here, e.g. the French terms-->\n\n====Verb====\n{{en-verb}}\n\n# {{lb|en|transitive|slang}} To bring into [[prison]], to [[roof]].\n#* {{quote-song|en|composer=CDM|lyricist=ZK & Digga D|year=2017|title=No Hook|passage=Free Criminal, he got '''birded'''<br/>That's a L but I know he’ll firm it<br/>I was vexed when I heard that verdict}}\n\n=====Derived terms=====\n{{col|en|bird off}}\n\n=====Translations=====\n{{trans-top|to bring into prison, to roof}}\n* French: {{t+|fr|taule|f}}<!-- these may belong to the box above-->\n* German: {{t-check|de|absitzen im Cafe Viereck}}\n* Swahili: {{t+check|sw|ndege}}\n{{trans-bottom}}\n\n===References===\n* {{R:Online Etymology Dictionary}}\n* {{pedia}}\n* {{comcatlite|Aves}}\n* {{specieslite|Aves}}\n* {{R:OneLook}}\n\n===Anagrams===\n* {{anagrams|en|a=bdir|drib}}\n\n{{topics|en|Birds|Vertebrates}}\n{{catlangname|en|words derived through metathesis}}\n\n==Middle English==\n\n===Noun===\n{{head|enm|noun|altform=1}} \n\n# {{lb|enm|late}} {{alt form|enm|brid}}"}}